This is a really cool feature. I much prefer it to the Tribes page. 
---Maybe put the "Top Commanders" above the "Most Recent Decks" section? Opening the Infect page we see five Atraxa in a line. People using this feature are probably looking for ideas about what kinda of commanders are popular for infect before they want to see the individual lists. 
---The +1/+1 counter and -1/-1 counter pages produces error 404 Not Found. 
---I'd use a different card than Etherium-Horn Sorcerer to represent Random. Maybe Whims of the Fates or something? Would also suggest naming it 'chaos' instead of 'random.' 
---The commanders under the "Top Commanders" section list below them the number of decks that fit the category. (Example, Oloro has 282 decks on the "Life" page. When you click on him, though, it takes you to the normal Oloro page, with 1478 decks. This might be confusing for users to see the two separate numbers; they might not understand that the 282 refers to the number of decks that meet the '>12 cards with keyword "life"' filter you set up.
---Some of the numbers on the filters may need tweaking over time as well; the creature tokens page, for example, shows a whole bunch of Top Commanders for creature token themes, but a lot of them have numbers below 50 decks. Just tuning over time.
---As a user, the categories I'm most interested in seeing expanded for this feature: artifacts; equipment; enchantments; superfriends; group hug; spell-heavy; mill. It also feels like the tribal page should go here too. I know some of these might be difficult to set up as filters, but they're the archetypes I'm personally most interested in seeing aggregated for this feature. 
---I'd also probably remove the -1/-1 counters as a category. Personal bias, maybe, but I haven't seen this as a deck archetype before, and given its overlap with Infect, it seems more complicated than entirely worth it. 

Hope this helps!
